---
// src/pages/legal.astro — Imprint + Privacy for datavism.org.
// Operator block adopted from data-snack (same controller, Frank Bültge).
// Privacy reflects datavism's actual data reality: no analytics, no cookies,
// no tracking, self-hosted fonts — the only personal-data flow is the optional
// waitlist email (double opt-in) via the SHARED data-snack drop-notifier backend.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import { ANALYTICS_ENABLED } from '../lib/analytics'

// BUILD GUARD (honesty coupling with Analytics.astro): this page currently states
// "no analytics, no cookies, no tracking". If the analytics env vars get set, the
// claim becomes false — so the build MUST fail until this policy is rewritten.
// To enable analytics: update the EN sections ("The short version", "7. Cookies &
// storage") and the DE sections ("Kurzfassung", "Cookies"), add the provider to
// the processors table, bump `updated`, then delete this guard.
if (ANALYTICS_ENABLED) {
  throw new Error(
    'legal.astro still claims "no analytics, no cookies, no tracking" but analytics is enabled ' +
      '(PUBLIC_UMAMI_SRC/PUBLIC_UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID are set). Update the privacy policy first — ' +
      'see the BUILD GUARD comment in src/pages/legal.astro.',
  )
}

const updated = '2026-07-11'
---
<Base title="Imprint & Privacy — DATAVISM" description="Legal notice, imprint and privacy policy for datavism.org. No tracking, no cookies, self-hosted fonts — only an optional double-opt-in waitlist email." footer={false}>
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="eb">// DATAVISM · LEGAL</div>
    <h1 class="font-display title">Imprint &amp; Privacy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: {updated}. English first; the German sections (Impressum / Datenschutz) are legally controlling for this German operator.</p>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2 class="font-display">// Site notice (§ 5 DDG)</h2>
      <div class="block">
        <p>Frank Bueltge<br />c/o Autorenglück #98451<br />Albert-Einstein-Str. 47<br />02977 Hoyerswerda<br />Germany</p>
        <p>Email: ghost@datavism.org<br />Website: datavism.org<br />Author: frankbueltge.de</p>
        <p>Responsible for content per § 18(2) MStV: Frank Bueltge, address as above.</p>
      </div>
      <p>datavism.org is the data-activism lab of the Data Underground — a non-profit digital art &amp; education project, sister site of <a href="https://data-snack.com">data-snack.com</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2 class="font-display">// Privacy policy</h2>
      <h3>The short version</h3>
      <p>This site runs <strong>no analytics, no cookies, no tracking</strong>, and self-hosts its fonts (no third-party CDN call). The only personal data we ever process is the email you voluntarily give us for the launch waitlist, and only with double opt-in.</p>

      <h3>1. Controller</h3>
      <p>Frank Bueltge, c/o Autorenglück #98451, Albert-Einstein-Str. 47, 02977 Hoyerswerda, Germany · ghost@datavism.org. A Data Protection Officer is not required under § 38 BDSG; contact the address above for any privacy request.</p>

      <h3>2. Server logs (essential)</h3>
      <p>When you load the site, our hosting provider automatically logs technical request data (truncated IP, timestamp, URL, status code, user agent, referrer domain). Purpose: operating and securing the site. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest). Retention: short-term (max. 14 days), then deleted.</p>

      <h3>3. Waitlist email (consent, double opt-in)</h3>
      <p>If you enter your email in the waitlist form, we send you one confirmation email. Only after you click the confirmation link is your address activated and stored — that is double opt-in. We then use it for <strong>exactly one purpose</strong>: a single email when the first line opens. No drip, no funnel, no profiling, no sale.</p>
      <p>Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent) and § 7(2) Nr. 3 UWG. You can withdraw at any time (link in every email, or write to ghost@datavism.org) with effect for the future.</p>
      <p>The waitlist is operated on the <strong>shared mail backend of our sister site data-snack.com</strong>: your address is held in one global contact pool, tagged into the <code>underground-waitlist</code> segment. The double-opt-in record (status, timestamp) is stored as the system of record in Google&nbsp;Cloud Firestore (EU region); delivery runs through Resend.</p>

      <h3>4. Processors &amp; recipients</h3>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Service</th><th>Provider</th><th>Location</th><th>Safeguard</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Hosting + waitlist proxy</td><td>Vercel Inc.</td><td>USA / EU edge</td><td>DPA · SCC · DPF</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Waitlist record (system of record)</td><td>Google Cloud (Functions, Firestore)</td><td>EU (europe-west)</td><td>DPA · EU storage</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Email delivery</td><td>Resend, Inc.</td><td>USA inc. · EU storage (eu-west-1)</td><td>DPA · SCC · EU storage</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3>5. Third-country transfers</h3>
      <p>Some providers above are US-incorporated. Transfers are safeguarded by EU Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC, 2021/914), the EU-US Data Privacy Framework where applicable, EU data storage, and data minimization. Residual risk under Schrems II / FISA 702 cannot be fully excluded; we mitigate it by collecting as little as possible (one email, with consent).</p>

      <h3>6. Your rights</h3>
      <p>You have the rights to access (Art. 15), rectification (16), erasure (17), restriction (18), portability (20), objection (21), and to withdraw consent (Art. 7(3)) at any time. Write to ghost@datavism.org. You may also lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority — for this operator: <em>Der Landesbeauftragte für Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit Mecklenburg-Vorpommern</em>.</p>

      <h3>7. Cookies &amp; storage</h3>
      <p>This site sets no cookies and no tracking storage. The only browser storage is a local self-check / waitlist flag that stays on your device and is never sent. There is therefore no cookie banner — there is nothing to consent to.</p>

      <h3>8. Minors</h3>
      <p>Intended for users aged 16+. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 16.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider">// DEUTSCHE VERSION · IMPRESSUM + DATENSCHUTZ (maßgeblich)</div>

    <section class="sec" lang="de">
      <h2 class="font-display">// Impressum (§ 5 DDG)</h2>
      <div class="block">
        <p>Frank Bueltge<br />c/o Autorenglück #98451<br />Albert-Einstein-Str. 47<br />02977 Hoyerswerda<br />Deutschland</p>
        <p>E-Mail: ghost@datavism.org<br />Website: datavism.org<br />Autor: frankbueltge.de</p>
        <p>datavism.org ist ein persönliches, nicht-kommerzielles Kunst- und Bildungsprojekt. Verantwortlich nach § 18 Abs. 2 MStV: Frank Bueltge, Adresse wie oben.</p>
      </div>
      <h3>Haftung &amp; Urheberrecht</h3>
      <p>Als Diensteanbieter bin ich gemäß § 7 Abs. 1 DDG für eigene Inhalte verantwortlich, nach §§ 8–10 DDG aber nicht verpflichtet, fremde Informationen zu überwachen. Für externe Links haften deren Betreiber. Eigene Inhalte unterliegen dem deutschen Urheberrecht.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="sec" lang="de">
      <h2 class="font-display">// Datenschutzerklärung · DSGVO</h2>
      <p><strong>Kurzfassung:</strong> Diese Seite nutzt <strong>keine Analyse, keine Cookies, kein Tracking</strong> und hostet ihre Schriften selbst (kein Dritt-CDN). Es gibt hier schlicht nichts zu tracken. Einzige Verarbeitung personenbezogener Daten: die freiwillig angegebene E-Mail für die Launch-Warteliste, ausschließlich per Double-Opt-in.</p>
      <p><strong>Verantwortlicher:</strong> Frank Bueltge, c/o Autorenglück #98451, Albert-Einstein-Str. 47, 02977 Hoyerswerda · ghost@datavism.org. Ein Datenschutzbeauftragter ist nach § 38 BDSG nicht erforderlich.</p>
      <p><strong>Server-Logfiles (essenziell):</strong> technische Zugriffsdaten (gekürzte IP, Zeit, URL, Statuscode, User-Agent, Referrer-Domain). Zweck: Betrieb und Sicherheit. Rechtsgrundlage: Art. 6 Abs. 1 lit. f DSGVO. Speicherung: kurzfristig (max. 14 Tage).</p>
      <p><strong>Warteliste (Einwilligung, Double-Opt-in):</strong> Nach Eingabe der E-Mail senden wir eine Bestätigungsmail; erst nach Klick auf den Link wird die Adresse aktiv gespeichert. Verwendung für genau einen Zweck: eine Mail, wenn die erste Linie öffnet. Rechtsgrundlage: Art. 6 Abs. 1 lit. a DSGVO, § 7 Abs. 2 Nr. 3 UWG. Widerruf jederzeit mit Wirkung für die Zukunft (Link in jeder Mail oder ghost@datavism.org). Betrieb über das <strong>geteilte Mail-Backend der Schwesterseite data-snack.com</strong> (geteilter Kontakt-Pool, Segment <code>underground-waitlist</code>; Double-Opt-in-Nachweis in Google Cloud Firestore, EU-Region; Versand über Resend).</p>
      <p><strong>Auftragsverarbeiter:</strong> Vercel Inc. (Hosting/Proxy, USA/EU, DPA·SCC·DPF), Google Cloud (Wartelisten-Datensatz, EU-Region, DPA), Resend, Inc. (Versand, US-Gesellschaft mit EU-Speicherung, DPA·SCC). Drittlandtransfers via SCC/DPF, EU-Speicherung und Datenminimierung abgesichert; Restrisiko nach Schrems II nicht vollständig ausschließbar.</p>
      <p><strong>Ihre Rechte:</strong> Auskunft, Berichtigung, Löschung, Einschränkung, Übertragbarkeit, Widerspruch, Widerruf der Einwilligung (Art. 15–21, Art. 7 Abs. 3 DSGVO) — ghost@datavism.org. Beschwerderecht bei der Aufsichtsbehörde: Der Landesbeauftragte für Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit Mecklenburg-Vorpommern.</p>
      <p><strong>Cookies:</strong> Es werden keine Cookies und kein Tracking-Storage gesetzt; daher kein Cookie-Banner.</p>
    </section>

    <p class="back"><a href="/">← back to the entrance</a></p>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 28px 80px; }
  .eb { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.2em; color: var(--color-eyebrow); margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .title { font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 52px); line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.04em; margin: 0; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .updated { font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-ink-4); margin: 16px 0 0; line-height: 1.6; }
  .sec { margin-top: 44px; padding-top: 28px; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge); }
  .sec h2 { font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(18px, 2.6vw, 24px); letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0 0 18px; color: var(--color-signal); text-transform: uppercase; }
  .sec h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ink); margin: 22px 0 8px; }
  .sec p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-ink-2); margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .sec a { color: var(--color-signal); }
  .sec code { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--color-line-g); }
  .block { border-left: 2px solid var(--color-edge-2); padding-left: 16px; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .block p { color: var(--color-ink); font-size: 14px; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; margin: 8px 0 12px; }
  table { width: 100%; text-align: left; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; }
  th { color: var(--color-ink-4); font-weight: 600; padding: 6px 12px 6px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge); }
  td { color: var(--color-ink-2); padding: 6px 12px 6px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge); vertical-align: top; }
  .divider { margin: 48px 0 8px; text-align: center; color: var(--color-ink-4); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.2em; }
  .back { margin-top: 44px; font-size: 14px; }
  .back a { color: var(--color-signal); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge-3); padding-bottom: 2px; }
</style>
